#. <section class="sutta" id="sn9.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.12:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga"
msgstr "1. In the Woods"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 12. Majjhanhikasutta → majjhantikasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts2) | majjhantiko (saṇika) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn9.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Majjhanhikasutta"
msgstr "12. Midday"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.438"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.12:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time one of the mendicants was staying in the land of the Kosalans in "
"a certain forest grove."

msgctxt "sn9.12:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā tassa bhikkhuno santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"The deity haunting that forest approached that mendicant and recited this "
"verse in their presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: majjhanhike → majjhantike (bj, s1-3, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn9.12:2.1"
msgid "“Ṭhite majjhanhike kāle,"
msgstr "“In the still of high noon,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sannisīvesu → sannisinnesu (si, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn9.12:2.2"
msgid "sannisīvesu pakkhisu;"
msgstr "when the birds have settled down,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.12:2.3"
msgid "Saṇateva brahāraññaṃ,"
msgstr "the formidable jungle whispers to itself:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.12:2.4"
msgid "taṃ bhayaṃ paṭibhāti maṃ."
msgstr "that seems so scary to me!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.12:3.1"
msgid "Ṭhite majjhanhike kāle,"
msgstr "“In the still of high noon,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.12:3.2"
msgid "sannisīvesu pakkhisu;"
msgstr "when the birds have settled down,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.12:3.3"
msgid "Saṇateva brahāraññaṃ,"
msgstr "the formidable jungle whispers to itself:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.12:3.4"
msgid "sā rati paṭibhāti man”ti."
msgstr "that seems so delightful to me!”"
